<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q21_v2" title="Q21_v2" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>
      En un plano, se dibuja un cuadrado cuya diagonal se calculó como 
      <m:math>
        <m:mfrac>
          <m:mn>4</m:mn>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msqrt>
        </m:mfrac>
      </m:math>
      metros. Para anotar esta medida, se decide escribir una expresión exactamente equivalente, pero sin raíz en el denominador. ¿Cuál de las siguientes expresiones representa la misma longitud?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>4</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al racionalizar, 4/√2 = (4×√2)/(√2×√2) = 4√2/2 = 2√2, no 4√2. Además, 4√2 es el doble de 2√2, así que no representa la misma longitud.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al racionalizar, 4/√2 = (4×√2)/(√2×√2) = 4√2/2 = 2√2. Esta expresión es exactamente equivalente y ya no tiene raíz en el denominador.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si 4/√2 fuera igual a 2, al multiplicar ambos lados por √2 se obtendría 4 = 2√2. Pero 2√2 es la forma racionalizada de 4/√2, no el número 2. Por lo tanto, 2 no es una expresión equivalente.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          </m:msqrt>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si 4/√2 fuera igual a √2, al multiplicar ambos lados por √2 se obtendría 4 = 2. Esa igualdad es falsa. Por eso, √2 no representa la misma longitud.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso: racionalizar el denominador</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la expresión dada</strong></p>
            <p>La diagonal está escrita como:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                <m:msqrt>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msqrt>
              </m:mfrac>
            </m:math>
            <p>Se pide una expresión exactamente equivalente, pero sin raíz en el denominador.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Racionalizar el denominador</strong></p>
            <p>Multiplicamos numerador y denominador por <m:math><m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math> para no cambiar el valor de la fracción:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mfrac>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msqrt>
                    <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Simplificar el denominador</strong></p>
            <p>Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, queda:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Simplificar la fracción</strong></p>
            <p>Dividimos 4 entre 2:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mfrac>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión equivalente a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:mfrac></m:math> es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es <strong>ChoiceB</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>